  {
    "client_msg_id": "803267b9-c65d-4282-a822-34ea6e5ab5ef",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "One test for whether something is reducible to money is: can you get equivalent results by paying someone vs finding someone directly involved. When it comes to giving feedback, the answer is no. And so it is, I'm increasingly convinced, with writing software in general. I don't have a solution to involve non-programmers. But it seems far more straightforward for us programmers to be more involved in the libraries we develop atop.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
